warehouse

Interface IWarehouse

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    Warehouse

    public interface IWarehouse
    Specifies the behavior of a warehouse where an assortment of IProducts is organized. The behavior is defined by several methods that allow to dynamically add, remove and update IProducts. Additionally, an Iterator can be returned to iterate through the managed IProducts.

    The warehouse will not deliver any objects references to stored products, only IDeepCopys of the objects will be passed.

    Author:
    OOP
